Don Hall is an American film director and writer at Walt Disney Animation Studios .
He is known for co-directing Winnie the Pooh -LRB- 2011 -RRB- , Big Hero 6 -LRB- 2014 -RRB- , which was inspired by the Marvel Comics of the same name and Moana -LRB- 2016 -RRB- , along with Ron Clements and John Musker .
Big Hero 6 won the Oscar for Best Animated Feature in 2015 .
Don is a graduate of the University of Iowa with a bachelor of fine arts degree in drawing and painting .